Another hurricane is heading our way - but rather than battening down the hatches, it might be time to reach for the sunglasses.

Hurricane Cristobal, which is gathering speed in the Bahamas, is forecast to narrowly miss Britain at the end of the week.

Experts say it will drag an area of high pressure behind it, creating a dry, warm and sunny start to September - a welcome relief after the end-of-August washout created spectacular scenes over the Seven Sisters cliffs in Sussex.

